{
  "text": "Ghrelin has been recognized to influence feeding behavior, energy homeostasis and also gastrointestinal functions [CITATION_1] . Various reports showed that body weight loss was accompanied with the increase in concentration of ghrelin [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Our results showed that treatment with EECCL not only increases adiponectin levels, but also that of ghrelin levels. The observation that EECCL supplementation to the obese rats resulted in the increase of plasma ghrelin and adiponectin were consistent with the results of Hsu et al. [CITATION_4] that reported the effects of green tea extracts in increasing the concentration of ghrelin and adiponectin in obese women.",
  "correct_citation": {
